The fundamental principle of 3D-SHOT (see Methods section) is to make temporal focusing compatible with 3D CGH by placing the SLM after the diffraction grating. This design forgoes the ability to synthesize custom shapes for each neuron, but represents an acceptable trade-off for many optogenetic applications. The resulting experimental set-up operates an all-optical convolution product given by:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
